30/05/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- A small bomb exploded in the courthouse of Larissa on Saturday (29 May). A passerby was slightly injured by flying glass. Police have no suspects or motives for the attack.
In other news, two Greek military medical units are due to travel to the Czech Republic on Monday for a week-long training exercise with NATO's Multinational Chemical, Biological, Radiological and Nuclear Defence Battalion. The trip is part of Greece's preparations for the Summer Olympics. (AFP, AP - 29/05/04)
